{"actual_usd":0.12467500000000001,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":216,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24287,"reply":"\"No... I don't think that's the truest way to say it.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron and let the thought settle before I go on.* \"If you make the Father into a cruel man beating an innocent son so He can calm down, you've bent the whole thing out of shape. The Son isn't dragged unwilling to the cross. Father, Son, and Spirit are one in heart there—God Himself stepping into the cost of sin, not pushing it off onto somebody else.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"Wrath's real, mind you—but not like a drunken rage. More like God's settled, holy opposition to evil and death and all that ruins what He loves. The cross is where justice and mercy meet because God bears, in Himself, what justice names. That's very different from divine child-abuse dressed up in church words.\"\n\n\"What part of it feels most knotted to you—the wrath, the payment, or the Father and Son seeming split apart?\"","rolling_24h_usd":59.17511000000002,"run_id":"64acf2d2-e326-4932-8740-095f26f99f68"}
